WEBVTT

00:15.116 --> 00:17.451
Previously on
Blunt Talk...

00:17.551 --> 00:19.053
I think I'm being followed.

00:19.153 --> 00:21.055
A colleague of mine,
he was on to something

00:21.155 --> 00:23.191
very corrupt here
in LA with the water.
He's dead.

00:23.291 --> 00:26.127
I haven't done anything
wrong lately, have I?

00:26.227 --> 00:29.863
You've yet
to respond to Vivian
and Moby's wedding invitation.

00:30.064 --> 00:31.332
This is all my fault.

00:31.432 --> 00:33.601
Oh, don't beat
yourself up, Walter.

00:33.701 --> 00:36.404
Not everything
is your fault.

00:36.504 --> 00:38.572
How do they do that?

00:38.672 --> 00:41.309
I mean, is there a hole
under the desk and they're
all climbing up a ladder?

00:41.409 --> 00:43.344
Ready, Jim? We have to
go to the hospital now.

00:43.444 --> 00:46.347
Okay. Did I just
swallow mescaline?
Yeah.

00:46.447 --> 00:48.116
Celia, will you marry me?

00:48.216 --> 00:49.583
I love you so much.
I really do.

00:49.683 --> 00:52.220
This is terrible.
Herschel, where's Cornelia?

00:52.320 --> 00:54.021
You know, I heard her
talking on the phone.

00:54.122 --> 00:55.623
She's meeting somebody
at the old depot.

00:55.723 --> 00:57.591
It seemed serious.

00:57.691 --> 01:00.228
This can't be good, Harry.

01:18.512 --> 01:20.548
Harry...!

01:20.648 --> 01:22.616
Sit down and try
to relax, Major.

01:22.716 --> 01:24.252
I'm not a major,
I'm a captain.

01:24.352 --> 01:25.619
And why do I need
to relax?

01:25.719 --> 01:28.322
Sorry, I was referring
to the major, Major.

01:28.422 --> 01:30.524
I mean captain,
Captain.
What?

01:30.624 --> 01:32.560
Who's the major?
He's the major, Captain.

01:32.660 --> 01:34.495
Uh, that's right,
I'm the captain, Major.

01:34.595 --> 01:36.230
Uh, I'm the major,
Captain.

01:36.330 --> 01:38.466
Christ, Harry,
you got me all muddled.

01:38.566 --> 01:40.701
I think you're both drunk.
I smell alcohol.

01:40.801 --> 01:43.237
I take offense to that
statement, Captain.

01:43.337 --> 01:44.605
I am perfectly sober.

01:44.705 --> 01:47.275
Maybe it's witch hazel
you can smell, Captain.

01:47.375 --> 01:48.609
We use it
for dry skin

01:48.709 --> 01:52.513
and, uh, other more
private ailments.

01:52.613 --> 01:54.582
Mr. Blunt.
Yes?

01:54.682 --> 01:57.285
We've located
your missing person.
She's at Cedars-Sinai.

01:57.385 --> 01:59.720
Somebody gave her
a good working over,
but she's conscious.

02:01.389 --> 02:04.392
Dr. Shapiro to Cardiac...

02:09.563 --> 02:11.232
I'll wait here, sir.

02:11.332 --> 02:13.434
Thank you, Harry.

02:26.447 --> 02:28.616
Oh, oh, oh!

02:30.818 --> 02:33.287
Walter.
Poor dear.

02:33.387 --> 02:35.656
I can't believe
this has happened.

02:35.756 --> 02:37.791
Are you in pain?

02:37.891 --> 02:40.494
Not too bad.
Good drugs.

02:40.594 --> 02:42.596
Almost makes it worth it.

02:42.696 --> 02:44.365
But how did you find me?

02:44.465 --> 02:46.133
I went to the police.

02:46.234 --> 02:48.636
Oh, Walter,
I'm so sorry
I worried you.

02:48.736 --> 02:51.138
If you had waited

02:51.239 --> 02:53.407
till the end of the broadcast,
I would have come with you.

02:53.507 --> 02:54.675
I could have protected you.

02:54.775 --> 02:57.311
But I was set up.

02:57.411 --> 03:01.349
Somebody is making a lot
of money off of this drought.

03:01.449 --> 03:03.050
And they don't want
people to know.

03:03.251 --> 03:05.152
Here we go.
Oh!

03:05.253 --> 03:08.622
Tony.
Walter, this is Tony.

03:08.722 --> 03:10.524
Tony, Walter.

03:10.624 --> 03:12.793
Hello.
Walter Blunt.

03:12.893 --> 03:15.296
I used to read
your column years ago.

03:15.396 --> 03:18.332
Oh.
Why did you use so many
exclamation marks?

03:18.432 --> 03:20.468
Tony, could you
give us a minute?

03:20.568 --> 03:23.537
Okay.
There's a clown
in the hallway.

03:23.637 --> 03:26.274
I'll pick his brain
for a good restaurant.

03:26.307 --> 03:27.441
...tech to Radiology.

03:27.541 --> 03:29.443
Imaging tech
to Radiology.

03:29.543 --> 03:32.646
So, um, who's Tony?

03:32.746 --> 03:35.616
We've been seeing each other
for the last six months.

03:35.716 --> 03:37.818
He flew here
to surprise me.

03:37.918 --> 03:40.554
I wanted to say
something sooner.

03:40.654 --> 03:43.724
It was just such
a shock to see you.

03:43.824 --> 03:46.294
Just tell me
how I can help you.

03:46.394 --> 03:48.662
There's nothing for you
to do, Walter.

03:48.762 --> 03:50.798
This is a fight
I can't win.

03:52.500 --> 03:55.603
Tomorrow, I'm going
back to England.

03:57.571 --> 04:01.342
I'm so sorry our timing
has never been right.

04:12.986 --> 04:17.358
Jesus Christ,
Jim's proposal's been reposted
half a million times.

04:17.458 --> 04:19.327
Where are all
the Shelly Tinkle GIFs?

04:19.393 --> 04:22.229
I know.
And I can't believe we
didn't think of Jimelia.

04:22.330 --> 04:24.197
I guess we've been
distracted by work.

04:24.398 --> 04:26.700
Jimelia.
Jim-elia.

04:26.800 --> 04:28.902
Jim-elia.

04:29.002 --> 04:31.339
It-- I mean, it's even
better than Brangelina.

04:31.405 --> 04:34.342
Or Kimye.
Or, uh-- or Billary.

04:34.408 --> 04:35.443
Or Sacher-Masoch.

04:35.543 --> 04:37.411
Who's Sacher-Masoch?

04:37.511 --> 04:39.347
Oh, I just threw
that in there.

04:39.380 --> 04:40.881
He invented masochism
in the 19th century

04:40.981 --> 04:43.584
and was a friend
to the Jews.
Oh.

04:43.684 --> 04:47.355
But do you think, uh, maybe
Celia will change her mind
and marry Jim?

04:47.388 --> 04:50.824
Oh, I hope not.
I'd still like to get
in her pants just once.

04:50.924 --> 04:54.395
What is it about her
that makes you so mad
with desire?

04:54.495 --> 04:56.430
I think
it's her long legs.

04:56.530 --> 04:59.733
She's like a tree
I want to topple.

05:01.569 --> 05:03.637
But I don't have an axe.

05:03.737 --> 05:06.907
I always want the ones
who don't want me.

05:07.007 --> 05:08.742
I have an axe.

05:08.842 --> 05:10.611
Shut up.

05:12.079 --> 05:14.382
Walter's not gonna
like this, Bob.

05:14.415 --> 05:15.616
Not at all.
No fucking way.

05:15.716 --> 05:17.718
You think I give a shit?

05:17.818 --> 05:20.621
Listen, this Jimelia
thing is huge.

05:20.721 --> 05:23.491
We've never had
a response like this.
Who gets 10,000 emails?

05:23.591 --> 05:27.294
Walter won't put them on-air
to discuss a private matter.

05:27.395 --> 05:29.830
He'll say Blunt Talk
is not a telenovela.

05:29.930 --> 05:34.502
Rosalie, lonely hearts
all across this country
are going nuts.

05:34.602 --> 05:38.572
It is a romantic story.
People want to know why
Celia won't marry him.

05:38.672 --> 05:40.641
You want to know, right?
Oh, yes, Mr. Bob.

05:40.741 --> 05:42.710
But Walter
won't have it!

05:42.810 --> 05:44.878
All I want
is a follow-up segment.

05:44.978 --> 05:46.880
They let our viewers know
that they are okay.

05:46.980 --> 05:49.450
Or not, which would
be even better, right?

05:49.550 --> 05:53.454
I-- I think it's huge.
I love it. I love it.
Mammy!

05:53.554 --> 05:56.890
Did you know Al Jolson,
aside from being one of the
greatest singers of his time,

05:56.990 --> 05:58.726
was also a huge
civil rights activist?

05:58.826 --> 06:01.629
No, I didn't
know that, Bob.
I like to sing.

06:01.729 --> 06:03.464
I love to sing.
I actually could
have been a star.

06:03.564 --> 06:05.566
I went to
the same high school
as Lenny Kravitz.

06:07.100 --> 06:10.037
You know, we should do
a bio piece on Al Jolson.

06:14.107 --> 06:17.511
If Walter gives you
a hard time about Jimelia
being on the air,

06:17.611 --> 06:19.880
you bring him to me
after my facial.

06:22.516 --> 06:24.985
Major,
anything I can do?

06:25.085 --> 06:26.820
Nothing, Harry.

06:26.920 --> 06:28.822
Those bastards.

06:28.922 --> 06:30.824
But she doesn't
want my help.

06:30.924 --> 06:32.059
She wants
nothing from me.

06:32.159 --> 06:33.761
I'm sorry, sir.

06:33.861 --> 06:35.596
And I know
that I am ridiculous,

06:35.696 --> 06:38.466
but I am heartbroken
again.

06:38.532 --> 06:41.001
And it's all
just projection, Harry.

06:41.101 --> 06:43.837
Most love is, sir.
What did Proust say?

06:43.937 --> 06:46.740
It is our imagination
that is responsible

06:46.840 --> 06:48.509
for love,
not the other person.

06:48.609 --> 06:50.944
I don't give a shit
about Proust, Harry.

06:51.044 --> 06:55.916
What pains me
is that she's with that
ass with the flowing hair.

06:56.016 --> 06:59.119
You have
a beautiful head, sir.
Like an artillery shell.

06:59.219 --> 07:01.855
So there's no need
to compare yourself
unfavorably

07:01.955 --> 07:03.056
to that dickhead
in the hospital.

07:03.156 --> 07:05.959
It's not about hair, Harry.

07:06.059 --> 07:09.497
I was never, ever
good enough for her.

07:15.603 --> 07:17.871
Walter, what's up?
It's early.

07:17.971 --> 07:20.541
I-- I want to come
and see you, Vivian.

07:20.641 --> 07:21.875
It's really important.

07:21.975 --> 07:23.611
What's wrong?

07:23.711 --> 07:24.878
You're not coming
to the wedding?

07:24.978 --> 07:28.081
Oh, Moby will be
so disappointed.

07:28.181 --> 07:31.118
He loves you.
It's not about Moby.

07:31.218 --> 07:33.521
Hey, Walter.
It's Moby.

07:33.587 --> 07:34.722
What's not about Moby?

07:36.123 --> 07:39.560
Oh, no, no, no.
No, no, no.

07:39.660 --> 07:41.128
Jim, please,
it's just a break.

07:41.228 --> 07:44.031
I need some time to think.
I need to breathe.

07:44.131 --> 07:46.700
You can think and you can
breathe and still be with me.

07:46.800 --> 07:49.637
I'm really sorry
I asked you to marry me

07:49.737 --> 07:52.139
while having
a hallucinogenic
experience, okay?

07:52.239 --> 07:54.608
I really am.
I'm sorry.

07:54.708 --> 07:56.109
It's not just that, Jim.

07:56.209 --> 07:58.846
I'm not good
at relationships.

07:58.946 --> 08:00.848
I feel like
I get erased.

08:00.948 --> 08:02.249
I only think
about you.

08:02.349 --> 08:04.585
Well, thinking
about me is good.

08:04.685 --> 08:07.555
- No, it's-- it's not.
- It's good.

08:07.655 --> 08:10.758
But if I hadn't asked you
to marry me, you wouldn't
be doing this.

08:10.858 --> 08:12.726
It may have pushed me
over the edge, yes.

08:13.861 --> 08:15.095
Over the edge?

08:15.195 --> 08:18.031
I hate myself.

08:18.131 --> 08:19.967
Jim, it's just
a break.

08:20.067 --> 08:22.670
Just some time for us
to, you know, think.

08:22.770 --> 08:24.572
This break might
give us perspective.

08:24.638 --> 08:27.007
It's just a break--
Stop saying "break."

08:27.107 --> 08:30.143
A break is just the first
step in breakup.

08:30.243 --> 08:32.079
Break-up.

08:32.179 --> 08:35.182
Break-up.
This is a breakup.

08:35.282 --> 08:37.651
Jim, please.
Let's be positive.

08:37.751 --> 08:39.887
Let's be grateful
that your-- your polyp
isn't cancerous.

08:39.987 --> 08:42.122
I don't care about
my stupid polyp.

08:42.222 --> 08:46.093
This has happened
to me before.

08:46.193 --> 08:49.597
It starts with a break,
then it's breakup.

08:49.697 --> 08:51.999
It's a break-up.

08:52.099 --> 08:54.167
A break-up.

08:54.267 --> 08:56.937
This is a break-up.
Jim!

08:59.106 --> 09:02.042
When will this...

09:02.142 --> 09:05.646
separation be over?

09:05.746 --> 09:07.715
I don't know.
You have to be patient.

09:07.815 --> 09:11.184
I really need you
to do this if you want
to hold on to us.

09:26.199 --> 09:28.268
Is it over yet?
Jim.

09:32.940 --> 09:35.308
Now?
Don't be silly.

09:39.179 --> 09:43.817
Now?
You know the break restarts
every time you ask that.

09:46.086 --> 09:49.289
I don't understand.
We covered this in
couples counseling

09:49.389 --> 09:51.058
for three years
and two months.

09:51.158 --> 09:55.195
Yeah, but I-- I never really
grasped what went wrong--

09:55.295 --> 09:58.131
why it didn't
work out.

09:58.231 --> 10:02.102
What in me
was lacking?

10:02.202 --> 10:04.104
Nothing.
Nothing.

10:04.204 --> 10:07.841
Uh, well, maybe it was
the late nights,

10:07.941 --> 10:10.778
the drinking,
your bathroom issues,
Harry.

10:10.878 --> 10:14.214
But deep down inside
I just knew I wasn't
the one for you.

10:14.314 --> 10:17.250
Daddy!
Hey, Bertie.

10:17.350 --> 10:19.319
Give us a hug.
Ah!

10:19.419 --> 10:22.255
Hey, why are you
wearing a yarmulke?

10:22.355 --> 10:25.358
Moby wants everyone
at the wedding to wear
a yarmulke.

10:25.458 --> 10:27.828
Hey, but Moby's
not a Jewish name.

10:27.928 --> 10:30.097
Ready or not,
here I come!

10:30.197 --> 10:33.166
Bertie! Walter, hi.
Hi, Moby.

10:33.266 --> 10:35.202
It's so good
to see you.
Yeah.

10:35.302 --> 10:37.104
Family.
No.

10:37.204 --> 10:39.406
Your show last night
was amazing.

10:39.506 --> 10:42.910
Thank you.
But are those two actually
gonna get married?

10:43.010 --> 10:44.978
I don't know
what's happening
with Jim and Celia.

10:45.078 --> 10:47.080
But, Moby,
why are you
getting everyone

10:47.180 --> 10:48.949
to wear yarmulkes
at your wedding?

10:49.049 --> 10:51.184
So I have this idea
that all of us

10:51.284 --> 10:53.353
are gonna wear
these shiny yarmulkes

10:53.453 --> 10:55.823
and there's gonna be
an aerial drone

10:55.923 --> 10:59.092
circling over the wedding
and with our yarmulkes

10:59.192 --> 11:00.794
we're gonna spell out

11:00.894 --> 11:04.131
"Moby loves Vivian."

11:04.231 --> 11:05.733
Oh.

11:07.367 --> 11:10.570
Well, I'm sorry to add
to your miseries, Walter,

11:10.738 --> 11:13.440
but I do have three
pieces of bad news.

11:13.540 --> 11:15.375
In what order
do you want them?

11:15.475 --> 11:18.111
Oh, start
with the least painful
and work your way up.

11:18.211 --> 11:22.182
Okay, one-- the jail
is on lockdown

11:22.282 --> 11:24.051
with a lice
outbreak.

11:24.151 --> 11:26.586
We have to reschedule
Duncan Adler.

11:26.754 --> 11:28.889
Fine, bump him.
We've done it before.

11:28.989 --> 11:30.824
That wasn't too bad.

11:30.924 --> 11:33.927
Two-- we heard
from the lawyer.

11:34.027 --> 11:37.931
Blunt Cock may be
harder than we think.
Oh, shit.

11:38.031 --> 11:42.135
Oh, I think we just may have
to swallow this one,
legally speaking.

11:42.235 --> 11:44.304
We have a meeting with
the lawyers next week.

11:44.404 --> 11:46.239
Coffee, Major?
Oh, yes, Harry.

11:46.339 --> 11:48.641
And three--

11:48.776 --> 11:51.444
Gardner wants
Jim and Celia
on air tonight

11:51.544 --> 11:54.214
to discuss last night's
marriage proposal.

11:54.314 --> 11:57.017
What?
Did you see this?

11:57.117 --> 11:59.452
Jimelia is on
the front page of Reddit.

11:59.552 --> 12:02.055
What the hell
is Jimelia?

12:02.155 --> 12:04.124
It's Jim and Celia's
power couple name.

12:04.224 --> 12:06.459
Although Celia has already
asked for a separation.

12:06.559 --> 12:08.695
The Today Show,
Good Morning America,

12:08.796 --> 12:11.131
they all had a good laugh
about it this morning.

12:11.231 --> 12:14.667
But we were trying
to raise consciousness
about colon cancer.

12:14.802 --> 12:17.971
Thank you, Harry.
I'm afraid it's been
overshadowed, Walter.

12:18.071 --> 12:20.673
And this is because
Jim went berserk.
Where is he?

12:20.808 --> 12:22.442
He went to run an errand
at the Dollar Shop.

12:22.542 --> 12:24.912
And Celia?
She's in the ladies'
room crying.

12:25.012 --> 12:28.115
And Shelly's consoling her,
if we can trust her motives,

12:28.215 --> 12:30.483
which I think we can.

12:30.583 --> 12:32.385
I think I've finished
crying.
Okay.

12:32.485 --> 12:35.055
Poor Jim.

12:35.155 --> 12:38.926
I once broke up
with someone and he killed
himself three years later.

12:39.026 --> 12:41.294
Oh, I-- I doubt
there was a connection.

12:41.394 --> 12:43.997
Wait, wait, wait.
Some more still needs
to come out.

12:45.398 --> 12:46.967
Celia.

12:47.067 --> 12:49.269
Please,
it's gonna be okay.

12:49.369 --> 12:51.404
I feel terrible
for hurting him.

12:51.504 --> 12:53.941
I'm an awful person.
Just awful.

12:54.041 --> 12:56.977
No, no, no, no, no.
You're not awful.

12:57.077 --> 12:59.179
Jim's gonna be all right.
He'll survive.

12:59.279 --> 13:01.314
But he's so fragile.
So are you.

13:01.414 --> 13:04.284
Listen...

13:04.384 --> 13:07.220
if I do something
funny right now,
will you stop crying?

13:07.320 --> 13:08.321
Like what?

13:11.224 --> 13:13.693
Guess who I am.

13:29.176 --> 13:32.045
Did you figure it out?
It's so easy.

13:32.145 --> 13:33.413
I've got no idea.
Get off the floor.

13:33.513 --> 13:35.048
You're covered
in micro-feces.

13:35.148 --> 13:37.117
Can't believe
you didn't get it.

13:37.217 --> 13:39.352
Isadora Duncan.

13:39.452 --> 13:41.088
Her scarf got caught
in the wheel of a car

13:41.188 --> 13:42.455
in the south of France
and she broke her neck.

13:44.524 --> 13:47.594
Okay, sorry, sorry.
Okay, look. Look.

13:47.694 --> 13:50.763
Jim's gonna
be all right.
I know it.

13:50.898 --> 13:53.000
He is a lot stronger
than we give him credit for.

14:15.655 --> 14:19.026
Bob, I cannot stress
strongly enough

14:19.126 --> 14:22.295
how much I do not
want to do this.

14:23.931 --> 14:25.465
You know, I should
be in front of the camera.

14:25.565 --> 14:28.201
My mother tells me
when I walk into a room,

14:28.301 --> 14:30.203
people take notice,
they always have.

14:30.303 --> 14:34.574
Bob, please, why
is this Jimelia nonsense
so important to you?

14:34.674 --> 14:37.644
Because our audience
wants to know and it's
a good story.

14:37.744 --> 14:41.414
But I don't think Jim
and Celia's love life
is newsworthy.

14:41.514 --> 14:43.383
I don't think
anyone's is.

14:43.483 --> 14:45.452
A private heartbreak

14:45.552 --> 14:47.454
should remain that--
private.

14:47.554 --> 14:49.122
Blunt Talk is not a--

14:49.222 --> 14:50.857
Telenovela.

14:50.958 --> 14:53.060
How did you know
I was gonna say that?

14:53.160 --> 14:54.294
I know everything.

14:54.394 --> 14:56.329
Oh, Bob, please.

14:56.429 --> 14:59.499
Oh, you know who will have
Jim and Celia on air?

14:59.599 --> 15:01.868
Don Lemon.

15:01.969 --> 15:04.972
He would not.
Yeah, he called
earlier today.

15:05.005 --> 15:07.440
He wants to do a satellite
interview with our Jimelia.

15:07.540 --> 15:10.243
What?
So if you won't have 'em on,
I'll give them to Don.

15:10.343 --> 15:12.812
Don and I did a cappella
back at Emory.

15:19.186 --> 15:20.553
Fuck!

15:24.257 --> 15:25.725
Bob won, Walter lost.

15:25.825 --> 15:27.860
Jim and Celia are doing
a two-minute segment.

15:27.995 --> 15:29.997
Well, you were never
gonna win anyway.

15:30.030 --> 15:31.598
He was only
indulging you.

15:31.698 --> 15:36.469
Walter,
your therapist and his
pussy are here again.

15:38.505 --> 15:41.641
Do you think she put
special extra emphasis

15:41.741 --> 15:43.876
on pussy
just to antagonize me?

15:44.011 --> 15:47.447
