Detach with disinterest.

16:36.829 --> 16:38.498
I think
it's detach with love.

16:38.598 --> 16:40.900
I went to Al-Anon because
of my college roommate.

16:41.068 --> 16:43.436
He drank beer
every weekend.

16:43.536 --> 16:45.905
Whatever.
I'm detaching.
I have work to do.

16:46.106 --> 16:48.508
Hey, um, I was thinking.

16:48.608 --> 16:52.579
Uh, if we were a power couple,
our name could be Shartin.

16:52.679 --> 16:54.747
Oh, Shartin?
Yeah.

16:54.847 --> 16:56.583
A shit you thought
was a fart.

16:56.683 --> 16:58.518
Uh...
Cool.

16:58.618 --> 16:59.986
You're right.
That doesn't work.

17:00.087 --> 17:03.090
Um, uh,
what about, uh,
Martinelly?

17:03.156 --> 17:06.093
You know, that way, we'd have
our own apple juice.

17:06.159 --> 17:09.329
Uh, I found one in the fridge.
Do you wanna share it?

17:09.429 --> 17:12.932
No, Martin, I don't
want apple juice.

17:13.100 --> 17:15.535
I'm not a baby.
Get back to work.

17:15.635 --> 17:19.539
Jim and Celia
are useless morons today
and Walter needs us.

17:19.639 --> 17:21.374
I have so many regrets.

17:21.474 --> 17:23.910
My first wife,
my third wife,

17:24.111 --> 17:26.479
my second wife,

17:26.579 --> 17:29.682
Cornelia, Vivian.

17:29.782 --> 17:32.219
I've loved too much

17:32.319 --> 17:33.820
or I've loved
too little.

17:33.920 --> 17:38.658
Troubled people love
in a troubled way, Walter.

17:38.758 --> 17:41.694
Perhaps, then,
this is a time
to help others.

17:41.794 --> 17:43.863
You know, it's often
at our own nadir

17:44.131 --> 17:46.466
we can be
our most useful.

17:46.566 --> 17:49.536
I was thinking,
perhaps if you--

17:53.140 --> 17:56.309
Beth? Doctor?

17:56.409 --> 17:59.712
I will check on you
every hour, Dr. Mendelson.

17:59.812 --> 18:02.482
Thank you, Walter.
I won't bill you
for the full session.

18:02.582 --> 18:04.317
Oh.

18:04.417 --> 18:06.353
I hope
he'll be all right.

18:06.453 --> 18:08.755
Poor Beth.

18:08.855 --> 18:12.159
First Dr. Weiss,
now Dr. Mendelson.

18:12.225 --> 18:14.461
You're killing off
all your Jewish shrinks.

18:14.561 --> 18:17.530
Their being Jewish,
Rosalie, has nothing
to do with it.

18:17.630 --> 18:19.732
Help!

18:19.832 --> 18:21.434
I think
it's Jim, Major.

18:21.534 --> 18:23.703
Help!

18:23.803 --> 18:26.406
Help. Help.

18:26.506 --> 18:29.176
Jim. Jim.

18:29.209 --> 18:30.710
Walter, what are you
doing here?

18:30.810 --> 18:32.479
You were crying
for help.

18:32.579 --> 18:35.648
I was?
Oh, my God,
he's hoarding again.

18:35.748 --> 18:38.351
Harry, Martin,
help me.

18:38.451 --> 18:39.886
Come on, Jim.
Sit up.

18:39.986 --> 18:43.456
There we go.
Harry, commanding officer.

18:45.458 --> 18:47.194
Here.

18:49.462 --> 18:51.398
Jim, you all right?
Oh, no, no, no.

18:51.498 --> 18:52.832
Don't look at me.
I'm ugly.

18:52.932 --> 18:54.467
Rosalie, get her
out of here.

18:54.567 --> 18:57.237
All of you.
I'm so sorry, Jim.

19:00.840 --> 19:03.210
What's going on, Jim?

19:05.712 --> 19:07.747
Celia broke up
with me

19:07.847 --> 19:10.217
'cause I'm perverted
and I'm ugly.

19:10.283 --> 19:12.785
You're not perverted
and ugly.

19:12.885 --> 19:16.489
Anyway, I was under
the impression this
was just a break.

19:16.589 --> 19:18.625
That's what
they all say, Walter.

19:18.725 --> 19:20.960
It starts with a break,
then it's break-up.

19:21.228 --> 19:22.929
Break-up.
Break-up.

19:23.029 --> 19:25.064
It's a breakup.
Uh, stop it, Jim.

19:25.298 --> 19:26.866
I'm sorry.

19:26.966 --> 19:31.070
I know you're in pain.

19:31.271 --> 19:33.506
And I also understand

19:33.606 --> 19:36.643
the wretched sting
of rejection.

19:36.743 --> 19:39.446
But we have to accept

19:39.546 --> 19:42.882
we cannot control
another person's heart.

19:42.982 --> 19:45.252
We can't?
No.

19:45.285 --> 19:47.254
And everything's
gonna be all right.

19:47.320 --> 19:50.056
You're gonna
be all right.

19:50.257 --> 19:52.725
I am?
Mm-hmm.

19:54.327 --> 19:56.496
Will I get
Celia back?

19:56.596 --> 19:59.466
Uh, that
I can't promise.

19:59.566 --> 20:02.769
Sometimes...

20:02.869 --> 20:05.505
we lose people.

20:05.605 --> 20:09.108
The past 24 hours has been
an emotional roller coaster

20:09.208 --> 20:11.911
and we're both very touched
by the outpouring of concern

20:12.011 --> 20:13.780
after last night's
broadcast.

20:13.880 --> 20:16.983
But it was
premature of me to ask
Celia to marry me.

20:17.083 --> 20:19.686
We've only been dating
for three months.

20:19.786 --> 20:22.955
So we're going
to take a little break
to figure things out.

20:23.055 --> 20:25.157
But let's not forget
why this happened.

20:25.258 --> 20:27.627
If you're over 50,
you should get
a colonoscopy.

20:27.727 --> 20:30.897
It could save your life.
Or break your heart.

20:32.699 --> 20:34.701
We'll-- we'll send it
over to Walter.

20:34.801 --> 20:36.303
Thank you, Celia.
Thank you, Jim.

20:36.403 --> 20:39.339
I applaud your courage
and your honesty.

20:39.439 --> 20:43.376
Now, let's get back
to the news.

20:43.476 --> 20:46.946
They shouldn't
be alone tonight.

20:47.046 --> 20:50.850
I agree.
I'll take Jim,
you take Celia.

20:50.950 --> 20:53.953
At least Martin
and Shelly are stable.

20:54.053 --> 20:57.590
Yeah, my beautiful
Martin.

20:57.690 --> 20:59.359
Hmm.

20:59.459 --> 21:01.027
What about you,
Walter?

21:01.328 --> 21:04.331
Stable?
No!

21:04.397 --> 21:07.767
Not stable.
Not at all.

21:08.968 --> 21:10.803
I'm unglued.

21:10.903 --> 21:13.940
What's Harry say?

21:14.040 --> 21:15.742
Oh, Harry.

21:15.842 --> 21:17.710
He's off
in Sylvialand.

21:19.111 --> 21:22.214
Oh, I'm so
frustrated, Rosalie.

21:22.349 --> 21:26.353
Tonight's broadcast
was humiliating.

21:26.386 --> 21:28.921
And I do nothing
while Cornelia

21:29.021 --> 21:31.691
is terrorized
and chased out of LA.

21:31.791 --> 21:34.694
So do something.

21:34.794 --> 21:36.863
Show this woman
you love her,

21:36.963 --> 21:39.366
but expect nothing
in return.

21:39.432 --> 21:43.202
Hmm.
Can we flip over now?

21:43.370 --> 21:47.073
With Teddy away,
I need some affection.

21:47.374 --> 21:48.741
Yes, Rosalie.

21:53.913 --> 21:57.484
Oh, yes.

21:58.918 --> 22:01.053
"To put it concisely,

22:01.153 --> 22:03.923
we suffer
when we resist the noble

22:04.023 --> 22:07.894
and irrefutable truth
of impermanence and death."

22:09.596 --> 22:11.598
Well, I think
we'll stop there.

22:13.466 --> 22:14.967
Thanks, Harry.

22:15.067 --> 22:16.836
